Package musicSerialization

Klasse Album

java.lang.Object
musicSerialization.Album
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable
public class Album extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a music album with metadata and pricing information.

This class is serializable and can be converted to and from a string representation using a semicolon-delimited format.

  • Konstruktordetails

    • Album

      public Album(double price, String releaseDate, String label, int numberOfTracks, String name, int artistID, int albumID)
      Constructs a new Album instance with the given properties.
      Parameter:
      price - the price of the album in the local currency
      releaseDate - the release date of the album (e.g., "YYYY-MM-DD")
      label - the record label that published the album
      numberOfTracks - the total number of tracks on the album
      name - the title of the album
      artistID - the unique identifier of the artist
      albumID - the unique identifier of the album

    • fromString

      public static Album fromString(String data)
      Creates an Album instance by parsing a semicolon-delimited string.

      Expected format: albumID;artistID;name;numberOfTracks;label;releaseDate;price

      Parameter:
      data - the semicolon-delimited album data string
      Gibt zurück:
      a new Album object with fields populated from the data string
      Löst aus:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the data string is invalid or parts cannot be parsed
